eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 20 Years
Maximum age: 60 Years
This trial does not accept healthy volunteers.
As per self-report or review of the patient’s medical record, if the patient is taking anti-depressant medication, fewer than three months on anti-depressant medication
Active hepatitis or human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) infection.

groups.description: Patients undergo fractionated TBI BID on days -7 to -4 and receive etoposide IV over 4 hours on day -3. Patients undergo allogeneic PBSCT on day 0 and receive GVHD prophylaxis as in Regimen I.

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material
Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

groups.name: Regimen II (AML, MDS, CML, ALL, lymphoma, myeloma)

groups.description: DNA extracted from previously collected tumor samples is analyzed to validate the clinicopathologic associations and prognostic significance of ATR mutation.
groups.name: Basic science (DNA analysis)

outcome_measures.measure: Percentage of Participants with CR, Determined by an Independent Review Committee (IRC) on the Basis of Positron Emission Tomography (PET) and Computed Tomography (CT) Scans
outcome_measures.time_frame: Within 6 to 8 weeks after Day 1 of Cycle 6 (up to approximately 23 weeks) (1 cycle:21days)

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Kaplan--Meier method will be used to analyze RFS time.
outcome_measures.time_frame: Time from date of response until the date of first objective documentation of disease-relapse, assessed up to 5 years

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Will explore whether knowledge-based planning (KBP) can improve IG-IMRT plans compared to plans that would have been delivered without KBP, estimate the resulting toxicity reduction using normal tissue complication probability (NTCP) models, and determine whether KBP should be a requirement for future IG-IMRT protocols
outcome_measures.measure: Type of intensity modulated radiation therapy (IG-IMRT)

outcome_measures.analysis_method: A repeated measures analysis of variance will be used to assess the effect across time points.
